// Vitest Snapshot v1, https://vitest.dev/guide/snapshot.html

exports[`snapshot — timeline entry body /timeline/2026-04-16-published-relational-timeline-entry/ > renders a stable <main> body for the timeline entry detail page 1`] = `"<main class="w-100 w-75-ns pa4 lh-copy"> <header class="mb4"> <p class="f6 ttu tracked theme-midtone mt0 mb2"> <time datetime="[DATE]">April 16, 2026</time> </p> <h1 class="f2 lh-title mt0 mb3">feature: Published the first threaded timeline update</h1> </header> <heading-anchors> <p>Published the first follow-up entry in the new threaded timeline model.</p> <p>Timeline entries can now point back to earlier entries, which turns the feed into more of a build log than a flat list. This update continues from the original timeline launch and marks the point where parent and follow-up relationships became part of the feature.</p> <p>The implementation for this lives in <a href="https://github.com/TheClooneyCollection/11ty-subspace-builder/pull/17">PR #17</a>.</p> </heading-anchors> <section class="timeline-thread"> <div class="timeline-thread__branch timeline-thread__branch--parent"> <p class="timeline-thread__label">Earlier in thread</p> <div class="timeline-thread__stack"> <article class="timeline-entry timeline-entry--compact timeline-entry--muted" data-type="shipped"> <div class="timeline-dot" aria-hidden="true"></div> <div class="timeline-body-wrap"> <div class="timeline-topline"> <span class="timeline-handle">Nicholas Clooney</span> <time class="timeline-timestamp" datetime="2026-04-14T15:42">April 14, 2026 · 15:42</time> </div> <h2 class="timeline-title"><a href="/timeline/[DATE]-shipped-timeline/">feature: Shipped the timeline page</a></h2> <div class="timeline-content"><p>Added a personal timeline feed to the site. Markdown files in <code>timeline/</code>, same front matter as posts. Color is tag-driven: <code>shipped</code> goes green, <code>published</code> goes blue, <code>thinking</code> goes amber — no extra fields needed.</p> </div> <div class="timeline-footer"> <div class="timeline-tags"> <a href="/timeline/subspace/">#subspace</a><a href="/timeline/timeline-page/">#timeline-page</a> </div> </div> </div> </article> </div> </div> </section> </main>"`;
